<div id="review_2122035693" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2122035693" />
    <a title="Peter Tillman" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8101737-peter-tillman"><img alt="Peter Tillman" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607621390p2/8101737.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2122035693?book_show_action=true">Sep 12, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Peter Tillman" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Peter Tillman" href="/user/show/8101737-peter-tillman">Peter Tillman</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780671475529" href="/book/show/100466.The_Dragon_Waiting">review of another edition</a>


          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Peter by: </span>
      Jo Walton's review
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8101737-peter-tillman?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8101737-peter-tillman?shelf=hist-fiction">hist-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8101737-peter-tillman?shelf=reread-list">reread-list</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8101737-peter-tillman?shelf=award-win-nom">award-win-nom</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2122035693" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7309798235845192394">Good news: Tor is publishing a new edition the end of this month (Sept. 2020) of this hard-to-find masterpiece.<br/><br/>Off to a 5-star start with this World Fantasy Award-winner that I&apos;d somehow missed. Publisher compares it to Mary Stewart&apos;s &quot;Crystal Cave.&quot; Not a bad call. &quot;Dragon&quot; sprawls from Ireland to Constantinople in the waning years of the Byzantine (Eastern Roman) Empire, which fell to the Turks in 1453, in OTL. Well, it&apos;s not waning *here* (see Jo Walton&apos;s review, linked below). Ford says he t</span>
  <span id="freeText7309798235845192394" style="display:none">Good news: Tor is publishing a new edition the end of this month (Sept. 2020) of this hard-to-find masterpiece.<br /><br />Off to a 5-star start with this World Fantasy Award-winner that I'd somehow missed. Publisher compares it to Mary Stewart's "Crystal Cave." Not a bad call. "Dragon" sprawls from Ireland to Constantinople in the waning years of the Byzantine (Eastern Roman) Empire, which fell to the Turks in 1453, in OTL. Well, it's not waning *here* (see Jo Walton's review, linked below). Ford says he tried hard to get the history right, up to the point of divergence, before adding the fantastic elements (wizards and vampires, so far). Then he quotes Nennius, whoever he was (ah, a Welsh monk of the 9th century): "I yield to him who knows more of these things than I do." Heh. <br /><br />[p.98. Dr Cecily Vittori is saving Lorenzo de' Medici's life]. You know you're in good hands when you tear up over bad stuff that happened six centuries ago. And when you slow down your reading, so you won't finish the book too soon.<br /><br />It's always a little startling when the words-in-a-row turn into people you care about. Author Ford was a little in love with Dr. Cecily, I think -- though he gave her some very hard knocks.<br /><br />The review to read is Jo Walton's,<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.tor.com/2009/07/30/subtle-history-john-m-fords-the-dragon-waiting/">https://www.tor.com/2009/07/30/subtle...</a><br />"It’s a brilliantly written, absorbing book with great characters; it’s hard to put down once it gets going; and it’s laugh aloud funny in places. This is John M. Ford’s World Fantasy Award-winning masterpiece...<br /><br />The characters are wonderful, all the way through. The book gives you time to get to know them and then uses them in precise ways, so you feel they’re doing exactly what they would do. This is true even of minor characters. It also uses Arthurian motifs to underscore the story, without ever getting tangled up in them. ... What a good book this is, what an enjoyable read, and how incredibly clever. I love it."<br /><br />Almost everyone who's read this book remarks on the need to reread it, to really understand what Ford was doing. For sure there are pages where I was wondering what the hell was going on. On the future-reread list. Amazingly dense and well-crafted book. 5 stars; almost certainly his masterpiece. RIP Mr. Ford (1957-2006). He died way too young.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7309798235845192394" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


