<div id="review_3604207865" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3604207865" />
    <a title="Micah Hall" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/62216141-micah-hall"><img alt="Micah Hall" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1608383611p2/62216141.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3604207865?book_show_action=true">Dec 06, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Micah Hall" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Micah Hall" href="/user/show/62216141-micah-hall">Micah Hall</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781250794802" href="/book/show/53359449-the-dragon-waiting">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3604207865" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8307041186273615098">4.25/5<br/><br/>There have been some interesting articles written about John M. Ford, chronicling his unfortunate disappearance from the literary world. This book won the World Fantasy Award when it came out but has been out of print for years until Tor gained the rights to publish it under their Tor Essentials line. <br/><br/>The novel centers on a cast of characters encompassing a wizard, a mercenary warrior, a vampire, and a physician who are attempting to stave off the Byzantine expansion westard in the 16th ce</span>
  <span id="freeText8307041186273615098" style="display:none">4.25/5<br /><br />There have been some interesting articles written about John M. Ford, chronicling his unfortunate disappearance from the literary world. This book won the World Fantasy Award when it came out but has been out of print for years until Tor gained the rights to publish it under their Tor Essentials line. <br /><br />The novel centers on a cast of characters encompassing a wizard, a mercenary warrior, a vampire, and a physician who are attempting to stave off the Byzantine expansion westard in the 16th century. At the start the novel has an interesting world in which Christianity and Roman expansion doesn't occur but the Byzantine empire persists and worship of multiple deities continues. This allows for imaginative "what-if" scenarios and world building.<br /><br />John M. Ford is an excellent wordsmith and his background as a poet really shines through. There are passages that are full of beauty and true works of art. I think where Ford really shines is his ability to create a sentence at the length it needs to be, avoiding bloat but remaining elegant (unlike these reviews). Furthermore, he has a nice ability to create memorable characters that grow on you as the novel progresses; I felt something for each of the characters involved. <br /><br />Caveats include a bit of a background on The War of the Roses or general European history in the 16th century; at times I felt a bit lost but it didn't ruin my entertainment. <br /><br />It sucks we lost such a talent early on and I hope we can now appreciate his work a bit more. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8307041186273615098" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


