<div id="review_3786678482" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3786678482" />
    <a title="Chad D" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/102005742-chad-d"><img alt="Chad D" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3786678482?book_show_action=true">Jan 24, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Chad D" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Chad D" href="/user/show/102005742-chad-d">Chad D</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3786678482" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17914029599713305316">Rating somewhere between four and five stars for subjective reasons; my life was not changed, the book did not assault or affirm my fundamental values or heart strings. But this book is very high quality alternative history, real people (both historical and fictitious) moving and suffering and loving in a substantial late-medieval world. The language is gravely beautiful; the world is built out of fragments of our own put back together in fantastic shapes.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


